What is RDS?

RDS is a managed relational database service in AWS.
It supports databases like MySQL, PostgreSQL, MariaDB, Oracle, and SQL Server, and handles the operational heavy-lifting for you.

Key point: You don‚Äôt manage OS, backups, replication ‚Äî AWS does it.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Why use RDS instead of self-managed DB on EC2?
		
		Self-managed DB (EC2)							RDS
		
		Install, configure, patch OS & DB yourself		AWS handles OS & DB setup, patches, backups
		Manual backups & monitoring						Automated backups & monitoring
		Manual replication for HA						Multi-AZ replication built-in
		Harder to scale									Easy to scale vertically & read replicas for horizontal read 	                                                 scaling


Interview line:

	‚ÄúRDS reduces operational overhead and improves reliability.‚Äù


#########  Key Features You Must Know

1Ô∏è‚É£ Multi-AZ deployment ‚Üí Fault tolerance

Primary DB in one AZ, standby in another AZ

Automatic failover if primary fails

2Ô∏è‚É£ Read Replicas ‚Üí Scalability

Offload read-heavy workloads

Can be in same or different region

3Ô∏è‚É£ Automated backups & snapshots ‚Üí Recovery

Daily backups + point-in-time recovery

4Ô∏è‚É£ Security

VPC isolation

Encryption at rest (KMS) & in transit (SSL)

5Ô∏è‚É£ Monitoring

CloudWatch metrics for CPU, memory, connections, etc.



#######

High Availability vs Scalability in RDS

Aspect	How RDS Helps

High Availability				Multi-AZ deployment ‚Üí automatic failover
Scalability						Read replicas ‚Üí offload read queries, vertical scaling ‚Üí bigger instance

Golden line:

‚ÄúRDS handles HA via Multi-AZ and scales reads via read replicas.‚Äù


5Ô∏è‚É£ Common RDS Interview Traps

# Single AZ vs Multi-AZ

	Single AZ ‚Üí downtime if AZ fails

# Multi-AZ ‚Üí automatic failover ‚Üí HA

	Read Replica vs Multi-AZ

# Read Replica ‚Üí scalability (read-only)

	Multi-AZ ‚Üí fault tolerance & HA

# RDS instance stops vs terminates

	Stop ‚Üí retains data, can start later

	Terminate ‚Üí data deleted unless snapshot taken

# Backup retention period

Usually configurable (1‚Äì35 days)


###  Interview-Perfect Answer (Memorize)

‚ÄúAWS RDS is a managed relational database service that handles patching, backups, and replication. Multi-AZ deployments provide high availability by automatically failing over to a standby instance, while read replicas allow horizontal scaling for read-heavy workloads.‚Äù

üî• Bonus One-Liner (Strong)

‚ÄúRDS reduces operational overhead, ensures fault tolerance, and provides easy scalability for cloud applications.‚Äù


######  RDS Multi-AZ vs Read Replica

| Feature             | Multi-AZ Deployment                 | Read Replica                       |
| ------------------- | ----------------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| **Purpose**         | High availability / fault tolerance | Read scalability                   |
| **Data flow**       | Synchronous replication             | Asynchronous replication           |
| **Writes allowed?** | Yes, only to primary                | No, read-only                      |
| **Failover**        | Automatic if primary fails          | Not for failover (used for reads)  |
| **AZ/Region**       | Usually same region, different AZ   | Can be same or different region    |
| **Use case**        | Prevent downtime due to AZ failure  | Offload read-heavy queries         |
| **Cost**            | Higher (standby instance running)   | Additional instance cost for reads |
